5m, 10m, 20m, 30m, 40m and 50m with respect to the centreline of the road. From Figure 18, it can be seen that GPS and the integrated system have similar actual Ô¨Åx density, where more than 55% are in 5m of accuracy and almost 100% are within 50m. Note however, that GPS has 90% coverage while the integrated system had 100 % coverage. On the basis of this, it is clear that the integrated (GPS/DR) system employing low cost DR devices performs better than GPS alone in providing continuous positioning with an accuracy of better than 50m.

